context: The format of a T20 cricket match is 20 overs per side.
A T20 match consists of 20 overs per side.
Chris Gayle holds the record for the fastest century in T20 cricket.
Afghanistan holds the record for the highest team score in a T20 match with 278/3.
Shakib Al Hasan has taken the most wickets in T20 cricket.
Virat Kohli has scored the most runs in T20 internationals.
A powerplay in T20 cricket is the first six overs of the innings where fielding restrictions apply.
There are 11 players in a T20 cricket team.
Mahendra Singh Dhoni captained the Indian team in the first T20 World Cup.
The number 200 is often seen as a challenging target to chase in T20 cricket.
India won the first T20 World Cup in 2007.
South Africa hosted the first T20 World Cup.
Aaron Finch holds the record for the highest individual score in T20 internationals with 172.
There are 6 balls in an over.
The wicketkeeper's role in T20 cricket is to stand behind the stumps and catch the ball if the batsman misses or edges it.
A 'dot ball' in T20 cricket is a delivery that results in no runs being scored.
LBW stands for 'Leg Before Wicket' in cricket.
The first T20 international was played between Australia and New Zealand in 2005.
A Super Over is used to determine the winner in case of a tie in a T20 match.
The IPL stands for Indian Premier League, a professional T20 cricket league in India.
Lasith Malinga is known for his unorthodox bowling action and success in T20 cricket.
Brendon McCullum scored the first-ever T20 international century.
West Indies has won the T20 World Cup twice, in 2012 and 2016.
The term 'yorker' refers to a ball bowled so that it lands at the batsman's feet, often aimed at the base of the stumps.
A free hit is awarded to the batting team after a front-foot no-ball is bowled.
Dew can affect the grip of the ball in T20 cricket, making it harder for bowlers to control their deliveries.
Kevin O'Brien scored the fastest century in a T20 World Cup match.
The Big Bash League is a professional T20 cricket league in Australia.
The 'death overs' refer to the final few overs of an innings in T20 cricket.
An 'all-rounder' is a player who excels at both batting and bowling.
Sunil Narine is known for his mystery spin bowling in T20 cricket.
Jasprit Bumrah is known for his ability to bowl yorkers consistently in T20 cricket.
The powerplay in T20 cricket restricts the number of fielders outside the 30-yard circle to two.

A 'hat-trick' in cricket is when a bowler takes three wickets in consecutive deliveries.

A boundary is when the ball crosses the edge of the field, scoring four runs if it hits the ground first and six runs if it doesn't.
